author: sascharodekamp
msg: UPDATE: Ajax callings in CheckoutProcess.js are not handling server-side errors correctly (https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OFBIZ-4342) A patch from Jonatan Soto: All methods that do ajax calls in CheckoutProcess.js are not dealing with the server-side errors. They should be treated in the success callback using an existing method called getServerError(data). This method looks for the _ERROR_MESSAGE* keys of the JSON object returned by the server.
